summary: saw Detective Pikachu... still sorting out my feelings about it but[[MORE]] did the final (final final. the last one) twist feel...
body:
saw Detective Pikachu… still sorting out my feelings about it but

did the final (final final. the last one) twist feel like… not right to anyone else? like im still not sure but… kinda felt wrong that they spent all of this time establishing a bond between Tim and Pikachu as partners, only to reveal Pika wasn’t Pika at all. Like I mean… well, maybe that’s just me but… a bond between pokemon and their people is such a central theme to most Pokemon media, and the movie certainly delivered on it throughout, so it felt weird to have it suddenly turn around and go “well actually…”

summary: I’M THINKING ABOUT MAKING AN ASMR VIDEO It’ll be a Roleplay video (Naturally) The theme is gonna be “Pokemon Cafe” The character...
body:
I’M THINKING ABOUT MAKING AN ASMR VIDEO

It’ll be a Roleplay video (Naturally)

The theme is gonna be “Pokemon Cafe”

The character I’ll be playing is gonna be a retired Pokemon professor and the overall vibe is gonna be basically “Japanese cat cafe but with Pokemon”

It’ll be filled with tons of little refernces and homages to the anime and games, there’s gonna be a Jigglypuff singing softly in the background.

I wanna get all the way into character, to the point of helping you chose a starter Pokemon from one of the various regions 

Then, about ten minutes in just as you’re on the verge of falling asleep.

L U D I C O L O

(I’m joking about this obviously, the idea just made me chuckle when I thought of it

body:
ATTENTION ALL POKÉMON FANS. THIS IS NOT A DRILL. I REPEAT THIS IS NOT A DRILL.

MOVIES LIKE SING AND THE SECRET LIFE OF PETS HAVE OFFICIALLY MADE MORE MONEY AT THE BOX OFFICE THAN DETECTIVE PIKACHU. IS THAT BULLSHIT? YES. IT IS. DETECTIVE PIKACHU DESERVES A PLACE IN THE TOP 200 HIGHEST GROSSING FILMS OF ALL TIME. RIGHT NOW, IT’S NOT EVEN ON BOX MOJO’S TOP 700.

SO WHAT DO WE NEED TO DO?

WE NEED TO SEE IT SO MANY TIMES IT GETS PUT ON THAT LIST.

HERE’S SOME INCENTIVE:

APPARENTLY, THERE IS A SHINY PIKACHU THAT OCCURS ONLY ONCE IN EVERY 15,537 SHOWINGS.

YOU WANNA SEE SHINY PIKACHU? OF COURSE YOU DO.

SO GET YOUR BUTT INTO THE THEATER, ALONG WITH A FRIEND OR A FAMILY MEMBER.
